From George Brown Subject Re PCX In article Jason Wiggle writes From Jason Wiggle Subject PCX Date Wed Apr GMT Hello HELP please I am a student of turbo c and graphics programming and I am having some problems finding algorithms and code to teach me how to do some Where is there a book or code that will teach me how to read and write pcx dbf and gif files How do I access the extra ram on my paradise video board so I can do paging in the higher vga modes ie anybody got a line on a good book to help answer these question Thanks very much send reply's to P Peace be Blessed be Stephen Palm A book that I can somewhat recommend is Pratical Image Processing in C by Craig Lindley published by Wiley It addresses reading writing to from PCX TIFF files image acquisition manipulation and storage and has source code in the The source is primarily written in Turbo C and naturally has conversion I have converted some of it to Quick Naturally the code has some problems in the book as Typos syntax are It can be a good learning experience for someone who is studying There is also a companion disk with source available for order and Overall the book is not I acquired the book at